                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_k0yr-_3" n="3" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>k˳yr-</orth><form type="variant">(<orth>-k˳yl</orth>)</form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kur-</orth><form type="variant">(<orth>-kul</orth>)</form></form><re><re><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в словах, обозначающих дефекты тела: </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in words denoting body defects: </note><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>k˳yræfcæg</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kuræfcæg</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>короткошейный</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>with a short neck</q></tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cænk˳yl</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>безрукий</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>armless</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сухорукий</q></tr></sense></sense></re></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Сближается с элементом %iкърн-%i, %iкур-%i, %iкар-%i в некоторых славянских терминах, выражающих телесные дефекты; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>корноухий, курносый, кургузый, карзубый</w></mentioned> и др. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>669</biblScope></bibl>). На арийской почве ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/> <w>karūdatin-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>krw-δntʼk</w> <gloss><q>карзубый</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Henning._Sogd."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>kaurva-</w> <gloss><q>дефектный</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is close to the element %iкърн-%i, %iкур-%i, %iкар-%i in some Slavic terms, which denote body defects; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>корноухий</w> <gloss><q>crop-eared</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>курносый</w> <gloss><q>snub-nosed</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>кургузый</w> <gloss><q>dock-tailed</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>карзубый</w> <gloss><q>without (frontal) teeth</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>669</biblScope></bibl>). On Aryan context cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/> <w>karūdatin-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>krw-δntʼk</w> <gloss><q>without (frontal) teeth</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Henning._Sogd."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>kaurva-</w> <gloss><q>defect (adj.)</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>